                        "Approach 1 (read-time SQL merge) vs approach 2 (write-time fan-out to per-user mailboxes); Twitter chose write-time work because reads outnumber writes ~100:1.",
                        "Fan-out is brutal at the tail: 75 followers avg means 345k writes/sec, but a 30M-follower user triggers 30M writes — so a hybrid exempts celebrities from fan-out.",
