                        "\n"
                        "**Are document databases repeating history?** This debate predates NoSQL. IBM's **IMS** (first released 1968, built for the Apollo program) used the **hierarchical model**: \"all data as a tree of records nested within records,\" much like JSON (p. 35). Like document DBs, IMS handled one-to-many well but made many-to-many difficult and had no joins — forcing developers to denormalize or manually resolve references (pp. 35-36).\n"
