                        "RPC evolution assumes servers upgrade first, so requests need backward and responses need forward compatibility; cross-org APIs force long-lived versioning.",
                        "Message brokers (Kafka, RabbitMQ) add buffering, redelivery and decoupling via one-way async topics; actor frameworks still require compatible encodings for rolling upgrades.",
