                        "Write skew updates different objects after reading a shared premise (doctors-on-call) — not a dirty write or lost update; only serializability prevents it automatically.",
                        "Phantoms (a write changing another query's result set) cause write skew when checking for absent rows; materializing conflicts is a last-resort workaround.",
