                        "The systems here are **shared-nothing**: machines that can only communicate over the network (p. 269). The internet and most datacenter networks are **asynchronous packet networks** — a node can send a packet, \"but the network gives no guarantees as to when it will arrive, or whether it will arrive at all\" (p. 270). When you send a request and wait for a reply, six things can go wrong (p. 270):\n"
