                        "\n"
                        "**Faults in practice** (p. 271): one study found about **12 network faults per month** in a medium datacenter, half disconnecting a single machine and half an entire rack. Redundant gear \"doesn't reduce faults as much as you'd hope\" because it doesn't guard against human error (misconfiguration). A switch software upgrade can delay packets for \"more than a minute\"; a NIC may drop all inbound packets while sending outbound fine (p. 271).\n"
