                        "This has **two bugs** (p. 287). First, it compares a lease expiry set on **another machine** against the local clock — if clocks differ by more than a few seconds, it misbehaves. Second, even using only a monotonic clock, it assumes little time passes between the check and `process(request)`. If the thread **pauses for 15 s** around `lease.isValid()`, the lease may expire and another node take over, yet this thread resumes and may \"have already done something unsafe by processing the request\" without realizing it slept (p. 287-288).\n"
                        "\n"
