                        "\n"
                        "**Truth is defined by the majority** (p. 292-293). A semi-disconnected node (outgoing messages dropped) or one stuck in a one-minute GC pause may be **wrongly declared dead** and be powerless to object — and the GCing node won't even realize a minute passed. So many algorithms use a **quorum**: decisions, including declaring nodes dead, are made by a **majority**. With 3 nodes you tolerate 1 failure; with 5 you tolerate 2. It is safe because \"there can only be only one majority in the system — there cannot be two majorities with conflicting decisions at the same time\" (p. 293).\n"
